      <lexlinks/>
      <example name="passivized" src="">
        <text>Some think Columbia 's thrift , which now is seeking a new chief operating officer , might be capitalized at , say $ 300 million , and shopped to a commercial bank that wants a California presence .</text>
        <propbank>
          <rel relloc="18">capitalized</rel>
          <arg type="ARGM-MOD" start="16" end="16">might</arg>
          <arg type="ARG1" start="2" end="14">Columbia 's thrift , which now is seeking a new chief operating officer</arg>
          <arg type="ARGM-DIS" start="21" end="21">say</arg>
          <arg type="ARG2" start="19" end="19">at</arg>
          <arg type="C-ARG2" start="22" end="24">$ 300 million</arg>
        </propbank>
      </example>
      <example name="active, no value" src="">
        <text>You sell the good bank as an ongoing operation and use some of the proceeds to capitalize the bad bank , '' says thrift specialist Lewis Ranieri of Ranieri Associates in New York .</text>
        <propbank>
          <rel relloc="16">capitalize</rel>
          <arg type="ARG0" start="0" end="0">You</arg>
          <arg type="ARG1" start="17" end="19">the bad bank</arg>
        </propbank>
      </example>
      <example name="Arg1" src="BOLT">
        <text>If the share price is 25.5 p per share , there are 68.37 million shares in issue and acording to ADVN the total market capitlisation is approx 17 million .</text>
        <propbank>
          <rel relloc="24">capitlisation</rel>
          <arg type="ARGM-ADJ" start="22" end="22">total</arg>
          <arg type="ARG1" start="23" end="23">market</arg>
        </propbank>
      </example>
